### Grid Container

The **grid container** defines the grid structure for its children.

---

### Creating a Grid Container

```css
.container {
  display: grid;        /* Block-level grid */
  display: inline-grid; /* Inline-level grid */
}
```

---

### Container Properties

| Property | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `grid-template-columns` | Define column sizes |
| `grid-template-rows` | Define row sizes |
| `grid-template-areas` | Named grid areas |
| `grid-template` | Shorthand for columns, rows, areas |
| `gap` | Spacing between cells |
| `column-gap` | Column spacing only |
| `row-gap` | Row spacing only |
| `justify-items` | Horizontal item alignment within cells |
| `align-items` | Vertical item alignment within cells |
| `justify-content` | Horizontal alignment of entire grid |
| `align-content` | Vertical alignment of entire grid |
| `grid-auto-flow` | How auto-placed items are inserted |

---

### Grid Template Columns

```css
/* Fixed sizes */
grid-template-columns: 200px 300px 200px;

/* Fractional units */
grid-template-columns: 1fr 2fr 1fr;

/* Mix */
grid-template-columns: 200px 1fr 200px;

/* Repeat function */
grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);

/* Auto sizing */
grid-template-columns: auto 1fr auto;

/* Minmax */
grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
```

---

### The `fr` Unit

`fr` = fraction of available space. Like `flex-grow` for grid.

```css
grid-template-columns: 1fr 2fr 1fr;
/* 1 + 2 + 1 = 4 parts. 25%, 50%, 25% */
```

---

### Repeat Function

```css
/* Without repeat */
grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr 1fr;

/* With repeat */
grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);

/* Repeat multiple patterns */
grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 200px 1fr);
```

---

### Minmax Function

```css
grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
/* Each column at least 250px, grows equally if space */
```

---

### Auto-Fit vs Auto-Fill

```css
/* Auto-fill: creates empty tracks */
grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(200px, 1fr));

/* Auto-fit: collapses empty tracks */
grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
```

> **Best Practice:** Use `repeat(auto-fit, minmax(minSize, 1fr))` for fully responsive grids without media queries.
